00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:42,880
We can put the name of the particle over here.

847
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:45,880
I'll put the symbol for the particle over here.

848
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:50,880
I'll put the particle type over here.

849
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,880
Now what do I mean by type?

850
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:54,880
I simply mean whether it's a fermion or boson.

851
00:37:54,880 --> 00:37:59,880
I'll put the electric charge over here.

852
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:06,880
There's another quantity which characterizes particles.

853
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,880
We'll call it the baryon number.

854
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:10,880
I'll tell you what it is.

855
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:11,880
It's a number.

856
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,880
I'll tell you what it is as we go along.

857
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:16,880
And there are other properties.

858
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:19,880
At the moment I'm not listing them.

