01:32:26,962 --> 01:32:28,962
So, there's the pi plus,

2137
01:32:28,962 --> 01:32:32,962
the four states here really define the three pi-ons,

2138
01:32:32,962 --> 01:32:35,962
pi plus, minus and zero,

2139
01:32:35,962 --> 01:32:37,962
and the eta meson.

2140
01:32:37,962 --> 01:32:39,462
The eta meson is similar

2141
01:32:39,462 --> 01:32:40,962
to a pi-on in many ways,

2142
01:32:40,962 --> 01:32:42,962
but it's heavier.

2143
01:32:42,962 --> 01:32:44,962
Why is it heavier?

2144
01:32:44,962 --> 01:32:46,962
That is a complicated story.

2145
01:32:46,962 --> 01:32:48,962
It's not an elementary story.

2146
01:32:48,962 --> 01:32:50,962
It's a complicated story.

2147
01:32:50,962 --> 01:32:52,962
Maybe we'll come to it, maybe we won't.

2148
01:32:52,962 --> 01:32:55,962
But, as a matter of fact,

2149
01:32:55,962 --> 01:32:58,962
its mass, okay, what are the masses of the pi-ons?

2150
01:32:58,962 --> 01:33:03,962
The masses of the pi-ons are about 140 MeV.

2151
01:33:03,962 --> 01:33:05,962
The mass of a pi-on,

2152
01:33:05,962 --> 01:33:07,962
mass of pi-on,

2153
01:33:07,962 --> 01:33:09,962
m pi,

2154
01:33:09,962 --> 01:33:13,962
is about 140 MeV.

2155
01:33:13,962 --> 01:33:15,962
So, in other words, it's not too different,

2156
01:33:16,962 --> 01:33:18,962
from,

2157
01:33:18,962 --> 01:33:20,962
question?

2158
01:33:20,962 --> 01:33:22,962
Yeah, it's about 140 MeV.

2159
01:33:22,962 --> 01:33:25,962
So, it's somewhere in this range in here,

2160
01:33:25,962 --> 01:33:27,962
not this heavy,

2161
01:33:27,962 --> 01:33:29,962
and the mass of the eta

2162
01:33:29,962 --> 01:33:32,962
is about three times heavier or something like that.

2163
01:33:32,962 --> 01:33:37,962
The mass of the eta is about 500 MeV.

2164
01:33:37,962 --> 01:33:39,962
I don't remember the precise number,

2165
01:33:39,962 --> 01:33:41,962
but that's about right.

2166
01:33:41,962 --> 01:33:43,462
Why that is, why the

2167
01:33:43,462 --> 01:33:44,962
eta sticks out as being different,

2168
01:33:44,962 --> 01:33:46,962
was a puzzle for a long time.

2169
01:33:46,962 --> 01:33:49,962
It's not obvious.

2170
01:33:49,962 --> 01:33:50,962
Not obvious.

2171
01:33:50,962 --> 01:33:55,962
Even today, it's a rather abstract mathematical fact,

2172
01:33:55,962 --> 01:33:57,962
but it is understood.

2173
01:33:59,962 --> 01:34:03,962
Isn't it also true that they're relatively long, half-lives?

2174
01:34:03,962 --> 01:34:04,962
Not very long.

2175
01:34:04,962 --> 01:34:06,962
How do you compare it to most of them?

2176
01:34:06,962 --> 01:34:10,962
The numbers of orders of magnitude difference?

2177
01:34:10,962 --> 01:34:12,962
Uh,

2178
01:34:12,962 --> 01:34:15,962
they don't decay by strong interactions,

2179
01:34:15,962 --> 01:34:17,962
they decay by weak and electromagnetic interactions,

2180
01:34:17,962 --> 01:34:22,962
so they're longer-lived than many of these other particles.

2181
01:34:22,962 --> 01:34:24,962
Yes, that is true.

2182
01:34:24,962 --> 01:34:26,962
They are long-lived.

2183
01:34:26,962 --> 01:34:29,962
Okay, that, those are the mesons.

2184
01:34:29,962 --> 01:34:31,962
Did you give a name to

2185
01:34:31,962 --> 01:34:33,962
the up bar, down down bar?

2186
01:34:33,962 --> 01:34:37,962
No, they don't have names by themselves.

2187
01:34:37,962 --> 01:34:39,962
They're a linear combination,

2188
01:34:39,962 --> 01:34:40,962
which are the sum and differences of them,

2189
01:34:40,962 --> 01:34:41,962
and have definite values.

2190
01:34:42,962 --> 01:34:43,962
Oh, I see.

2191
01:34:43,962 --> 01:34:44,962
Yes, those are...

2192
01:34:44,962 --> 01:34:46,962
Is that similar to...

2193
01:34:48,962 --> 01:34:51,962
Is that something like the neutrino oscillations?

2194
01:34:52,962 --> 01:34:54,962
Well, in the sense that it's

2195
01:34:54,962 --> 01:34:56,962
related to quantum superpositions of states, yes,

2196
01:34:56,962 --> 01:35:00,462
but it's got more to do

2197
01:35:00,462 --> 01:35:03,962
with spin combinations of two half-spin particles.

2198
01:35:04,962 --> 01:35:07,962
There are two ways that you can entangle...

2199
01:35:07,962 --> 01:35:08,962
Well, we'll come to it next time.

2200
01:35:08,962 --> 01:35:10,962
The last thing I simply want to tell you

2201
01:35:10,962 --> 01:35:12,962
is that you can make strange objects.

2202
01:35:12,962 --> 01:35:14,962
You can make strange mesons.

2203
01:35:14,962 --> 01:35:17,962
You can take any d-quark and

2204
01:35:17,962 --> 01:35:20,962
replace it by a strange quark,

2205
01:35:20,962 --> 01:35:23,962
strange bar quark, and so forth.

2206
01:35:23,962 --> 01:35:27,962
That makes new mesons, which are called strange mesons,

2207
01:35:27,962 --> 01:35:30,962
or what's the other name for them?

2208
01:35:30,962 --> 01:35:32,962
K mesons.

2209
01:35:32,962 --> 01:35:35,962
K mesons are mesons containing

2210
01:35:35,962 --> 01:35:38,962
a strange or an anti-strange quark,

2211
01:35:38,962 --> 01:35:40,962
replacing a down quark.

2212
01:35:40,962 --> 01:35:42,962
Okay?

2213
01:35:42,962 --> 01:35:44,962
There are four of them.

2214
01:35:47,962 --> 01:35:50,962
Up bar strange,

2215
01:35:51,962 --> 01:35:53,962
up strange bar,

2216
01:35:54,962 --> 01:35:56,962
down bar strange,

2217
01:35:56,962 --> 01:35:59,962
down strange bar.

2218
01:36:00,962 --> 01:36:02,962
These two have charge zero.

2219
01:36:03,962 --> 01:36:05,962
Charge zero.

2220
01:36:05,962 --> 01:36:08,962
And these have charge plus one and minus one.

2221
01:36:08,962 --> 01:36:10,962
These two are called the charged K mesons.

2222
01:36:10,962 --> 01:36:12,962
These two are called the neutral mesons.

2223
01:36:12,962 --> 01:36:15,962
The neutral K mesons.

2224
01:36:15,962 --> 01:36:18,962
So there are three kinds of pions,

2225
01:36:18,962 --> 01:36:20,962
one kind of eta,

2226
01:36:20,962 --> 01:36:22,962
and four kinds of...

2227
01:36:22,962 --> 01:36:23,962
How many does that make altogether?

2228
01:36:23,962 --> 01:36:25,962
Let's see.

2229
01:36:28,962 --> 01:36:31,962
Three pions,

2230
01:36:31,962 --> 01:36:33,962
four K mesons,

2231
01:36:33,962 --> 01:36:34,962
and an eta.

2232
01:36:34,962 --> 01:36:35,962
Yeah.

2233
01:36:35,962 --> 01:36:37,962
Yeah.

2234
01:36:37,962 --> 01:36:38,962
There's more.

2235
01:36:38,962 --> 01:36:39,962
There's more.

2236
01:36:39,962 --> 01:36:40,962
There's more.

2237
01:36:40,962 --> 01:36:42,962
Did we leave something out?

2238
01:36:44,962 --> 01:36:45,962
Yeah.

2239
01:36:45,962 --> 01:36:46,962
We left out one.

2240
01:36:46,962 --> 01:36:48,962
We left out some.

2241
01:36:48,962 --> 01:36:49,962
Yeah.

2242
01:36:49,962 --> 01:36:51,962
We left out s bar s.

2243
01:36:52,962 --> 01:36:53,962
Yeah.

2244
01:36:53,962 --> 01:36:54,962
There's nine.

2245
01:36:55,962 --> 01:36:56,962
Right.

2246
01:36:57,962 --> 01:36:58,962
Right.

2247
01:36:58,962 --> 01:36:59,962
Nine.

2248
01:36:59,962 --> 01:37:00,962
Nine altogether.

2249
01:37:00,962 --> 01:37:02,962
The reason it's nine is simple.

2250
01:37:02,962 --> 01:37:03,962
There are three kinds of quarks,

2251
01:37:03,962 --> 01:37:04,962
three kinds of anti-quarks.

2252
01:37:04,962 --> 01:37:06,962
Three times three is nine.

2253
01:37:06,962 --> 01:37:07,962
Yeah.

2254
01:37:07,962 --> 01:37:08,962
Right.

2255
